      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The first of 2 NARS races and SKY RIVER (7) goes on top for the local combination. The inside draw is a big tick for her chances having been edged out narrowly at York last time out when sitting on the speed. This is tougher, but she looks to get plenty of favours and she'll be hard to run down. PONY UP (5) is 60 days between runs but has turned in a decent trial since her latest effort. She's back to the mile today, but that shouldn't be an issue on the fresh side and she's shown plenty of ability in her recent efforts. May just be too good for her rivals. TRULY GALLANT (2) disappointed last start in a BM70+ at Geraldton last time out but he was in good order prior to that. Getting back up to the mile is a big tick for him now and he has plenty of upside. Looks poised to strike. SAXON JEWEL (6) steps out to the mile today and has to be included on her recent efforts. HARD SOLO (4) is another out in trip now, and her only run over this distance was in the WA Guineas. Include.",
